13 Sec. 4. (1) The Legislature finds that:
14 (a) Raw milk needs to be promptly processed;
15 (b) Lawful truck weight requirements can lead to an inability to
16 haul all available raw milk produced at a dairy farm, which results in
17 some raw milk being wasted;
18 (c) There has been a reduction in the availability of raw milk
19 processing facilities in this state; and
20 (d) The opportunity and need for overweight raw-milk vehicle permits
21 to operate overweight raw-milk vehicles to carry only raw milk from a
22 dairy farm to a milk processing facility for such raw milk is needed due
23 to 23 U.S.C. 127(a)(13), as such section existed on January 1, 2025,
24 concerning the carrying of fluid milk products.
25 (2) For purposes of this section:
26 (a) Bridge map means the map described in subsection (4) of this
27 section;
28 (b) Department means the Department of Transportation;
29 (c) Overweight raw-milk vehicle means a vehicle that has been issued
30 and currently holds an overweight raw-milk vehicle permit;
31 (d) Overweight raw-milk vehicle permit means a valid special,
-10-

LB561 LB561
2025 2025
1 continuing, or continuous overweight raw-milk vehicle permit issued under
2 section 60-6,298 to carry raw milk from a dairy farm to a processing
3 facility for such raw milk; and
4 (e) Prohibited bridge structure means a bridge structure identified
5 as prohibited on the bridge map.
6 (3) An overweight raw-milk vehicle shall:
7 (a) Not exceed a gross weight of one hundred seven thousand five
8 hundred pounds;
9 (b) For each single axle and each group of axles on the truck-
10 tractor and the hauling tanker trailer, not exceed the weight limits
11 calculated using the federal bridge formula identified in 23 U.S.C. 127,
12 as such section existed on January 1, 2025;
13 (c) Carry a physical or digital copy of the bridge map;
14 (d) Not enter any prohibited bridge structure; and
15 (e) Not travel on the National System of Interstate and Defense
16 Highways, unless authorized by the department on the overweight raw-milk
17 vehicle permit pursuant to written approval from the Federal Highway
18 Administration for such authorization.
19 (4)(a) Prior to January 1, 2026, the department shall create a map
20 of bridge structures in this state onto which an overweight raw-milk
21 vehicle shall not enter.
22 (b) The department shall review the bridge map at least once each
23 year and make any necessary updates to the bridge map.
24 (c) The department shall publish the most recent version of the
25 bridge map on the public website provided by the department.
26 (5)(a) The department may revoke the overweight raw-milk vehicle
27 permit for any overweight raw-milk vehicle that violates subsection (3)
28 of this section.
29 (b) Any such revocation shall not become effective until the holder
30 of any such revoked permit has been provided written notice by the
31 department of such revocation. Any such notice provided by United States
-11-

