1 mail is not effective until received by the holder of the revoked permit.
2 (c) Any such revocation may be appealed by the holder of the revoked
3 permit. The appeal shall be in accordance with the Administrative
4 Procedure Act.
5 (6) If the department determines that overweight raw-milk vehicle
6 permits put this state at risk of losing federal aid funding, the
7 department shall revoke all such permits.
8 (7) For any overweight raw-milk vehicle that enters a prohibited
9 bridge structure and is the proximate cause of damage to the prohibited
10 bridge structure, the owner of the overweight raw-milk vehicle shall be
11 liable for all costs associated with repairing such damage. The
12 department may bring an action to recover such costs associated with
13 repairing such damage in the district court of the county where the
14 prohibited bridge structure is located or in the district court of
15 Lancaster County. Any money recovered in such action shall be remitted to
16 the State Treasurer for credit to the Roads Operations Cash Fund.
17 (8) The department may grant an exception to section 60-6,290
18 regarding the length of a vehicle if such length is reasonable and is
19 needed for an overweight raw-milk vehicle to comply with all weight
20 limits for single axles and groups of axles.
